misc: It was originally named Aviation Siding, before being renamed to Aircraft Siding in 1972 and finally Aircraft in 1963.
The Western standard gauge line passes close by to the North of Platform 1.
Services going towards Melbourne may through-run with the Frankston line.

Bus.417: Laverton Station loop service via Laverton North

misc: It is the terminus for trains on the Alamein line.

It was known as Albion and Darlington until the 1st of January 1861, when the station was closed. A new station was opened to the west of the original station in 1891, which is when it became known as Albion. The station was then relocated to the site of the original 1860 station in late 1919.
The Melbourne – Sydney standard gauge line passes to the east of the station and, along with the Albion – Jacana freight line, branches off north of the station.
It is scheduled to rebuilt as part of the Airport rail link project (whenever [italic]that[/italic] happens)
